snippet.textDisplay:
> textfragments 

Normal links can link to specific elements on the page if they are marked with a unique (within the page) using a 'fragment' at the end of a URL. It's been this way for decades. The "problem" with it is websites have to actually add it manually.

TBH this is typical google chrome team - not trusting web developers and implementing half-assed workarounds to bad webpages that break far more functional ones than they fix, and generally cause more pain than necessary.
